               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_367-item1">
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Sharh-i Muqatta'at-i Anwani.</title>
                     <note>The initial entry is written in the Library copy of Codrington on a page inserted before p. 545. F1a; a) Two notes of ownership of Samad Shah Sahib. b) Four drafts for a chronogram for the death of a Sayyid Sa'd al-Din. 20 Muharram appears en clair in one version. The year not calculated. Final folio, verso: Two more notes of ownership of Samad Shah Sahib. A commentary on various points in the muqatta'at poems of Auhad al-Din Anwari. Headings and punctuation in red.</note>
                     <incipit>Baz in chih jawani u jamal ast jahan-ra For commentaries on the poetry of Anwari see Storey, v, (de Blois), pp. 225-6. The incipit of the Society's copy is different from that of the commentary on the muqatta'at by Mir Abu 'l-Hasan Farahani.</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>Storey, v, (de Blois), pp. 225-6.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
